        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 3700, 3800, 4600, 4700, 4800, 4900, 2554, 2654, 1652SC, and 8100 models with
                    DTA466.
                </para>
                <para>To improve alignment of the modulator cable on the above model vehicles, we have developed an
                    improved retention "Tee Nut" design at the accelerator rod anchor point of the modulator cable. It
                    will be necessary to enlarge the hole in the accelerator rod at the modulator cable position and
                    replace the original adjusting nuts with the "Tee Nut." Making this modification will allow the
                    modulator cable to maintain improved alignment as the accelerator rod moves through its arch from
                    idle to wide open throttle. This will prevent possible erratic shifting and/or overheating of the
                    transmission. This letter contains parts and service information to make this modification.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <para>To improve cable alignment on 1652SC, 37/3800, 46/47/48/4900 and 8100 with DTA466 engines, 2554, 2654
                Series, rework accelerator rod and install Tee Nut.
            </para>
