        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">SET THE PARKING BRAKE AND REMOVE THE IGNITION KEY TO INSURE THAT VEHICLE WILL NOT
                        BE MOVED DURING THIS PROCEDURE.
                    </emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the modulator cable from the accelerator rod and remove the adjusting nuts
                    from the cable. Discard the adjusting nuts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a 11/32 inch drill to enlarge the hole in the accelerator rod at the modulator cable
                    mounting position. With an up and down motion of the drill, elongate the hole (vertically)
                    approximately 30&#176; in both directions (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9312081">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Care must be taken not to damage the accelerator cable
                    during this operation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the modulator cable and adjusting sleeve in the elongated hole. Thread the
                    "Tee Nut" onto the adjusting sleeve to obtain cable end play of .060 to .100 inch at wide open
                    throttle (WOT) pedal position. Be sure to position the "Tee Nut" so it is 90&#176; to the
                    accelerator rod ("Tee Nut" must be horizontal).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten set screw in end of "Tee Nut" to engage the adjusting sleeve to prevent the "Tee
                    Nut" from coming loose or losing adjustment.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check operation of accelerator and modulator cables to insure that the modulator cable
                    alignment is satisfactory at both the idle and WOT position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check accelerator linkage to insure full throttle is attained with the pedal to the
                    floor (override is attained).
                </para>
            </step1>
